title: For Sale/Trade:  Heckler & Koch VP70Z 9MM
postcontent: I have a Heckler & Koch VP70Z 9mm  for sale or trade, this gun was the first polymer pistol produced and it's highly sought after by H & K fans, not to be confused with the VP70M which is the same gun but the slots on the shooters end for the detachable 3 shot burst butt stock have been filled in before importing, if you look closely you can see where the cutouts have been filled in the polymer grip and frame. Pretty interesting pistol here, this is definetly NOT a target pistol as the trigger is double action with a long slide before a crisp break, the gun has a slide safety behind the trigger but you could leave the safety off and never have to worry about it firing while you were carrying it. Straight blow-back operation (hammerless) with very deep rifling in the barrel to release gases for low and pleasing recoil. Gun was mfgd in 1981 and has been fired little, included are; original box, manual, test target, and one 18 rd. double stack magazine. title: For Sale:  LAZERMAX INTERNAL PISTOL LAZERS
location: OVRLAND PARK, KS, Kansas City, Kansas
postcontent:
Replaces the internal guide rod and spring and gun take down latch.
Simple installation – no gunsmith needed. As seen on Guns n Gear TV recently.

I mounted them on a SIG 226 and Beretta 92, ten years ago. I took the Beretta to an inside range about a year afterward and accidentally dropped it 42” to the concrete floor. Dings on the gun, but that lazer worked and worked for years afterward. 

They don’t have the problems of needing a special holster or accidentally turning on when in a holster. The on/off switch is ambidextrous. 

They have a big feature over Crimson Trace, which I also like – on the models with the lazer in the grip panels you can accidentally block the lazer when in safe condition with your finger off the trigger. That never happens with a Lazermax UNLESS you go crazy and start putting your hand in front of the barrel. Another great advantage is that they do not have to be adjusted for accuracy. The lazer is in the replacement guide rod which is inline with the barrel to work properly. Crimson Trace comes with mini Allen wrenches to keep them sighted in. They do eventually work loose. My cost was $265.

In the pic of inside the box there is nothing mssing. Only the parts for a particular pistol are put in the box.

Normal retail is $300 - $399 on most Lazermax pistol models.

Winchester Model 1894 custom order Saddle Ring .32 Win Special with crescent stock.  I ran the serial number and shows this rifle as being manufactured in 1932.  Barrel, Mag Tube, and wood in great condition with a shiny clean bore. No rust or cracks.  Also has a custom ordered adjustable rear peep sight.  The bluing on the receiver is gone but no rust or pits.  It has the brownish patina that is expected of these older Winchesters.  It has been inspected by a gunsmith and given the green light to shoot.  I love shooting this old rifle.  It is worthy being displayed above the fireplace or taken in the woods as a the deer slayer it was meant to be.  I will include 180 rounds.  The price of this rifle is $1,100. 

Second is my Henry Big Boy Lever Action .44 Magnum with octagon barrel.  I am the original owner of this immaculate rifle.  I fired 4 rounds through and it's been in the safe ever since. Bass Pro Shop sells them for $799.95.  The price on this one is $600.00.  That's a $200.00 savings.  

I will sell them individually at the price shown or as a package deal for $1,500.00.  That's an additional savings of $200.00 and the ammo is still included.
